description: Archived: The National Advisory Council (NTAC) is a 16 member group appointed by the U.S. Secretary of Education to Advise on State Standards, Assessments and Accountability Systems

Title: Sony Sample 1
description: Section 203 of Title II of the Educational Technical Assistance Act of 2002  (TA Act) directs the Secretary to establish twenty comprehensive centers to provide technical assistance to State educational agencies, local educational agencies, regional educational agencies and schools in implementing the goals and programs of NCLB.  In preparation for the new centers, Section 206 of the TA Act directs the Secretary to establish ten regional advisory committees to advise on the educational needs of each region.

Title: Sample PDF
description: The Assessment and Accountability Comprehensive Center (AACC) provides assistance to help students achieve high academic standards and to support the establishment of safe schools and healthy kids.
